
# Docker Notes: Containers, Networks, Bind Mounts, and Volumes

# 1. Installing Docker on Ubuntu

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
exit
```

## Important notes

After adding the user to the Docker group, logging out and logging back in is usually required so the group membership takes effect.

Without adding the user to the Docker group, Docker commands usually need `sudo`.

